text: {| |} MS Finlandia is a cruiseferry owned and operated by the Finnish ferry operator Eckerö Line. The ship operates between Tallinn and Helsinki. ==History== ==Sister ships== The Finlandia is the second of three identical ships built by DSME and Fincantieri.http://www.faktaomfartyg.se/moby_aki_2005.htm The other two ships are Moby Wonder and Moby Aki. Tallink’s Superstar is also considered a sister ship, but the two ships are not identical. ==References== Category:Ferries of Finland Category:2000 ships Category:Ships built by Daewoo Shipbuilding & Marine Engineering
